  "prompt": "Why do some people cry after sex?",
  "response": "There can be several reasons why some people cry after sex:\n\n1. Emotional release\n- Intense feelings of vulnerability \n- Overwhelming emotions\n- Psychological processing of intimacy\n\n2. Hormonal changes\n- Sudden drop in oxytocin and dopamine\n- Hormonal fluctuations can trigger emotional responses\n\n3. Past trauma\n- Unresolved emotional experiences\n- Triggers related to past sexual experiences\n\n4. Postcoital dysphoria (PCD)\n- A psychological condition causing unexplained sadness after sexual activity\n- More common than many people realize\n\n5. Deep emotional connection\n- Feeling of profound intimacy\n- Overwhelming sense of love or attachment\n\n6. Physical and emotional exhaustion\n- Physical and mental fatigue\n- Stress release\n\n7. Psychological factors\n- Anxiety\n- Unresolved relationship issues\n- Low self-esteem\n\nCrying after sex is not uncommon and can be a normal emotional response. If it happens frequently and causes significant distress, consulting a mental health professional might be helpful.",
